# Database Migrations (Flask-Migrate / Alembic)

## Daily workflow

```bash
cd backend

# After changing a model in models.py:
flask db migrate -m "short description of change"   # auto-generate migration
flask db upgrade                                     # apply to local DB
```

## First-time setup (existing database)

If you already have a populated `database.sqlite` from before Flask-Migrate
was introduced, run this **once** to register the current schema version:

```bash
flask db stamp head
```

After that, use the normal workflow above for all future schema changes.

## Fresh install

For a brand-new environment, `db.create_all()` in `app.py` will create all
tables on first startup. Then stamp:

```bash
flask db stamp head
```

Or skip `db.create_all()` entirely and let Alembic create the schema:

```bash
flask db upgrade
```

## Environment variables required

```bash
export SECRET_KEY=...
export JWT_SECRET_KEY=...
export ADMIN_INITIAL_PASSWORD=...   # only needed on first run
```
